{
  "type": "feat",
  "name": "Photosynthergy",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"va-quotation-text\"><em>The Intoxicating Petal grows strong beneath the Radiant Dawn.</em></span></p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.iwfbEXyacCnVLEoH]{Intoxicating Petal} maneuvers, two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.5w0wMZgWK1wxiZwL]{Radiant Dawn} maneuvers</p><p><strong>Benefit:</strong> As long as you maintain a Radiant Dawn stance, when a creature within 30 feet of you damages a creature with the sprout condition, they heal a number of hit points equal to the struck creature's sprout stacks plus the number of essence points invested in your Radiant Dawn stance. An individual creature can only heal this way once per round.</p><p>While you maintain an Intoxicating Petal stance, any healing you grant via a Radiant Dawn maneuver that damages a creature with sprout is increased by a number of hit points equal to twice that creature's sprout stacks, to a maximum amount of bonus healing equal to your initiator level.</p>",
      "instructions": ""
    },
